Meet <b>Cassie</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Cassie moved to her home at <a href='/home/?user=superkyanite'>5072 Eagle Circle</a> in Westridge on September 9th, 2004. Since then she's been enjoying all that Millsberry has to offer in a way that only she could. <br><br>Being both curious and friendly makes it pretty easy for Cassie to meet new people. It's the perfect recipe for a social butterfly. Her fascinating mix of interests also doesn't hurt either.<br><br>Cassie is interested in Math, Magic Tricks, and Animals, which should make her pretty good at calculating how long it takes to pull a rabbit out of a hat. It's a skill that not everyone possesses, but we know Cassie has what it takes to solve such complicated, and important, problems. <br><br>Halloween would most likely be Cassie's favorite day of the year. She has two Halloween challenge trophies, as well as a garden dedicated to the haunted holiday. We're sure this Halloween enthusiast will be well prepared next time October 31st rolls around. <br><br>Cassie also has awards from hitting the waves out at Okalani Island. Not only does she have a shiny Surfari trophy, but she also has the waxed boards to go with it. Don't worry about trying to be Cassie's knight in shining armor, because she's already got one of those in her guest room. <br><br>We also have to commend Cassie for being the fist person to put an indoor swimming pool in her bathroom. If you are washing up after a swim, try not to use the hot water, because you might melt the igloo that's also included in these marvelous facilities. <br><br>The next time you see Cassie, give her a high five and thank her for being such an outstanding citizen of Millsberry.</div>
